"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1934757-Eiffel-Tower-evacuated-Olympics-closing-ceremony\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower had to be evacuated after a shirtless man was spotted scaling the iconic Parisian landmark just hours before theOlympicsclosing ceremony today (Sunday).\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The daredevil was seen climbing the 1,083ft (330 metres) tall tower this afternoon, with his starting point unclear.\", \"from\": 170, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He was noticed just above the Olympic rings that adorn the second section of the monument, slightly above the first viewing deck.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At around 3pm, police ushered visitors away from the area, with some briefly trapped on the second floor before being allowed to leave about half-an-hour later.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 579, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Entry to the tower has been closed off.\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Video footage on social media showed the man just above the blue Olympic ring on the tower.\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 712, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Eiffel Tower, which was a focal point during the opening ceremony featuring Celine Dion, is not expected to play a part in the closing ceremony which is set to kick off at Stade de France in Saint-Denis at 8pm UK time.\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 936, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 794, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8828752784762963e-31, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 909, \"end\": 920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999732231121, \"rank\": 1.3647795386073093e-08, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will finish at around 10.30pm.\", \"from\": 937, \"to\": 970, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Billie Eilish, the Red Hot Chili Peppers and Snoop Dogg will all feature in the closing ceremony, as too couldHollywoodstar Tom Cruise.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1113, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 991, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Billie Eilish\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Billie_Eilish\"}, {\"begin\": 997, \"end\": 1018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Red Hot Chili Peppers\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Red_Hot_Chili_Peppers\"}, {\"begin\": 1023, \"end\": 1033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1102, \"end\": 1112, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's with Paris handing over the baton to Los Angeles for 2028.\", \"from\": 1114, \"to\": 1179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1126, \"end\": 1131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.807248111281557e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1158, \"end\": 1169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999547499111, \"rank\": 4.4908862420122966e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The incident at the Eiffel Tower comes as the Games draw to a close and security services shift their attention to the closing ceremony.\", \"from\": 1181, \"to\": 1317, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Over 30,000 police officers were deployed around Paris on Sunday, with Interior Minister Gerald Darmanin stating that around 3,000 officers would be mobilised around the Stade de France.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1368, \"end\": 1373, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.807248111281557e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1390, \"end\": 1407, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"score\": 0.9972003851467296, \"rank\": 0.00241502385849762, \"text\": \"Interior Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interior_minister\"}, {\"begin\": 1408, \"end\": 1414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"score\": 0.8649688787601075, \"rank\": 0.07283477908952839, \"text\": \"Gerald\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_South_Park_families\"}, {\"begin\": 1489, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An additional 20,000 police troops and other security personnel will be on duty late into Sunday night to ensure safety on the final day of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1507, \"to\": 1660, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB ended the competition seventhin the final medal tablewith 14 golds, 22 silvers and 29 bronzes.\", \"from\": 1662, \"to\": 1764, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1662, \"end\": 1669, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9597871222479138, \"rank\": 0.041115839965497454, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"China topped the standings with 40 golds.\", \"from\": 1765, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1765, \"end\": 1770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9982448134419616, \"rank\": 0.0011596227342122517, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1917, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding.\", \"from\": 1918, \"to\": 1994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can unsubscribe at any time.\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2027, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy Policy    Emma Finucane became the first British woman in 60 years to win three medals at a single Olympics with her bronze in the individual sprint on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2028, \"to\": 2203, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2085, \"end\": 2092, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999103863930322, \"rank\": 8.73851722769252e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 21-year-old reigning world champion added to her team sprint gold and keirin bronze.\", \"from\": 2205, \"to\": 2293, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2279, \"end\": 2285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.021889694664307e-29, \"text\": \"keirin\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Keirin\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Honestly, it's just like a dream,\\\" said Finucane.\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Obviously, I would have loved to win that gold medal, but gold and two bronzes is more than I could have dreamed of.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This week's been such a roller coaster.\", \"from\": 2464, \"to\": 2504, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wish I'd got a book for someone to tell me how to get through an Olympic week.\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have cried.\", \"from\": 2586, \"to\": 2599, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have had happy tears.\", \"from\": 2600, \"to\": 2623, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been exhausted and to get up every day and keep fighting, I am just really proud of myself.\", \"from\": 2624, \"to\": 2722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I gave everything for that bronze medal.\", \"from\": 2724, \"to\": 2765, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I just can not believe it's over.\", \"from\": 2766, \"to\": 2803, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am pretty sad, but it's just been such a whirlwind of a week.\\\"\", \"from\": 2804, \"to\": 2868, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 3039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3007, \"end\": 3020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1580929085182764e-16, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\", \"from\": 3041, \"to\": 3108, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3056, \"end\": 3069, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1580929085182764e-16, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"}]}]}"